<img src="NN220b"alt=" NN220b" width="500" " align="left" border="4" hspace="15" vspace="-15"   >   </a>


<font face="Technical"size="6">


Mrs. Santa's Sampler

<br><br>
</font>

<font face="Technical"size="5">
Mrs. Santa's Sampler is the merry companion to the popular Sampler Santa design from The Needle's Notion. 
<br><br>
Mrs. Santa is a needleworker and proudly holds her festive snowman sampler. 
Her cranberry red outfit features a golden sewing chatelaine at her waist. 
By her feet are a cozy cat and tomato pin cushion. All stitching and finishing instructions are included.
<br><br>
The design is worked on 28 count Amber/Toasted Almond Cashel Linen using DMC embroidery floss and Gentle Art threads. 
Additional craft supplies are required, and are listed on the chart.


<br><br>
Stitch Count: 178 wide by 165 high.
<br>
Finished Size: 5 inches wide x 10 1/2 inches tall

<br><br>
<br><br>

<font face="Technical"size="6">
Sampler Santa Stitching Supplies
<font face="Technical"size="5">
<br>


- 28 count Amber/Toasted Almond Cashel Linen, cut 18 x 18-inches
<br>

- DMC  floss: 310, 311, 352, 644, 647, 844, 945, 975, 3852 and White (2 skeins)
<br>

- Gentle Art Threads: Cranberry (35 yards), Bayberry (1 skein),  and Shutter Green (2 skeins)
<br>

Additional craft supplies for finishing Mrs Santa's Sampler are listed on the chart.


<br><br>


<b>

